Candidates can apply to a maximum of two positions and will be considered for jobs in the order you apply. The application limit is applicable to TikTok and its affiliates' jobs globally. Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis - we encourage you to apply early.

About the Team
The Microservice Framework team, based in Singapore focuses on in-depth research on programming languages, RPC frameworks, and high-performance middleware. We provide the company with research and development frameworks, high-performance middleware, service mesh, and unified Governance platforms. Among them, the Golang framework (Kitex) has been applied to tens of thousands of services carrying over billions of QPS in total and is at the forefront of the industry in terms of performance and scalability. Service Mesh and our traffic management platforms cover most of the company's businesses. You will have the chance to participate in cutting-edge research and development, working with our team to build the next generation of service communication frameworks.

Joining our department, you can look forward to growing and developing through ample opportunities in training and exposure. We look forward to your application! 

What you will be doing:
1. Develop, optimise, and maintain the RPC framework, improving performance, stability, and scalability issues;
2. Optimise the performance of microservices for business services, providing high-performance foundational components;
3. Build a new microservices architecture to solve existing problems in microservices. 

Qualifications

 What you should have:
- Final year or recent graduate with a background in Software Development, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or a related technical discipline;
- Interest in computer science and internet technology with high proficiency in at least one programming language, including but not limited to Golang, Java, Python, Rust;
- Familiar with RPC Frameworks / Service Mesh / Traffic Management Systems;
- Good understanding of RPC principles and frameworks such as Kitex / gRPC / bRPC / Dubbo / Thrift;
- Good understanding of network programming and protocols such as HTTP/HTTP2, TCP;
- Excellent problem-solving skills, able to effectively identify and address complex issues;
- Good teamwork skills, able to work effectively in a multitasking environment;
- Solid computer basic knowledge, in-depth understanding of data structure, algorithms, and operating system knowledge.

